00:26:44.180 --> 00:26:46.160
You will be needing
to give reports,

00:26:46.160 --> 00:26:48.600
because you have a bunch of
facts you need to deliver.

00:26:48.600 --> 00:26:52.000
I would encourage all of you
to never give a report again.

00:26:52.000 --> 00:26:54.870
I don't care what your
lead is asking for.

00:26:54.870 --> 00:26:56.290
Never give them a report.

00:26:56.290 --> 00:26:58.840
Nobody ever got a
raise, nobody ever

00:26:58.840 --> 00:27:01.380
got a promotion for giving
a really great report.

00:27:01.380 --> 00:27:04.340
What you will want to do is use
one of the other storylines.

00:27:04.340 --> 00:27:06.919
And you will couch
the facts within that,

00:27:06.919 --> 00:27:08.460
but that is the
storyline that people

00:27:08.460 --> 00:27:09.668
are going to find compelling.

00:27:09.668 --> 00:27:12.950
So, in a way, I would like
to encourage you from now on,

00:27:12.950 --> 00:27:16.406
anytime you need to give
a report, to maybe start

00:27:16.406 --> 00:27:18.530
to think about some of the
elements that take place

00:27:18.530 --> 00:27:23.380
in the storyline we're going
to explore now, the drama.

00:27:23.380 --> 00:27:28.940
If there was a patron
saint of presenters,

00:27:28.940 --> 00:27:31.020
it would be this
guy, Joseph Campbell.

00:27:31.020 --> 00:27:34.117
Now, I know many of you
know who Joseph Campbell is.

00:27:34.117 --> 00:27:36.700
Is there anybody in here who is
familiar with Joseph Campbell?

00:27:36.700 --> 00:27:38.320
Has anybody heard
of Joseph Campbell?

00:27:38.320 --> 00:27:41.290
So Joseph Campbell
was a historian.

00:27:41.290 --> 00:27:42.999
And he started working
in the late 1920s,

00:27:42.999 --> 00:27:44.998
and he worked all the way
up through, I believe,

00:27:44.998 --> 00:27:45.680
the early 1980s.

00:27:45.680 --> 00:27:47.930
And what Joseph Campbell did
is he traveled the world.

00:27:47.930 --> 00:27:50.990
He was fascinated
by the great myths

00:27:50.990 --> 00:27:53.472
of all of the great cultures
through all of history

00:27:53.472 --> 00:27:54.180
around the world.

00:27:54.180 --> 00:27:56.400
And he did is he went out
and he traveled around.

00:27:56.400 --> 00:27:58.730
And he learned to speak
seven different languages.

00:27:58.730 --> 00:28:00.130
He traveled all over the world.

00:28:00.130 --> 00:28:02.050
And he would get to
know the great myths

00:28:02.050 --> 00:28:03.300
from each one of the cultures.

00:28:03.300 --> 00:28:04.970
And what was really
fascinating is

00:28:04.970 --> 00:28:08.750
he started to realize that there
were a lot of common threads

00:28:08.750 --> 00:28:11.750
that existed between all
of these great myths in all

00:28:11.750 --> 00:28:13.390
of these different
languages from all

00:28:13.390 --> 00:28:15.654
of these different
cultures around the world.

00:28:15.654 --> 00:28:17.570
And one of the things
that Joseph Campbell did

00:28:17.570 --> 00:28:20.370
is he wrote a book called "The
Hero with a Thousand Faces."

00:28:20.370 --> 00:28:22.340
And what it was was
it's a big thick tome.

00:28:22.340 --> 00:28:24.890
It's his summary
of the commonality

00:28:24.890 --> 00:28:27.890
that he found between all
of these great world myths.

00:28:27.890 --> 00:28:30.400
And one of pieces
that was in that book

00:28:30.400 --> 00:28:33.570
is something that became
known as the hero's journey.

00:28:33.570 --> 00:28:35.830
And when Joseph Campbell
introduced this back

00:28:35.830 --> 00:28:38.134
in the 1950s, it didn't
really go anywhere.

00:28:38.134 --> 00:28:39.550
Nobody but a few
academics thought

00:28:39.550 --> 00:28:41.340
this was particularly
interesting.

00:28:41.340 --> 00:28:44.210
But since that time, for
reasons we will explore,

00:28:44.210 --> 00:28:46.710
this has become a really,
really common thread

00:28:46.710 --> 00:28:49.930
for how do we come up
with an interesting story.

00:28:49.930 --> 00:28:52.620
This is Joseph
Campbell's own drawing.

00:28:52.620 --> 00:28:55.640
He drew a little circle to
describe the hero's journey.

00:28:55.640 --> 00:28:57.890
And he drew the circle
moving in this direction,

00:28:57.890 --> 00:29:01.060
moving counterclockwise,
and it goes like this.

00:29:01.060 --> 00:29:05.710
We start at point X, at
which a hero, who's usually

00:29:05.710 --> 00:29:09.150
just a common person, crosses
from the regular world, which

00:29:09.150 --> 00:29:12.870
is above this line, into a
strange supernatural world,

00:29:12.870 --> 00:29:15.450
which is everything
below the line.

00:29:15.450 --> 00:29:19.470
In that supernatural
strange world at point Y,

00:29:19.470 --> 00:29:22.890
that hero encounters
fabulous forces.

00:29:22.890 --> 00:29:25.920
And the hero has to fight
an incredible battle

00:29:25.920 --> 00:29:29.500
to vanquish the foe to destroy
those forces in that very

00:29:29.500 --> 00:29:30.750
strange world.

00:29:30.750 --> 00:29:32.760
And then, having
learned the lessons

00:29:32.760 --> 00:29:35.720
of having fought that battle,
the hero then, at point Z,

00:29:35.720 --> 00:29:37.620
comes back into
the regular world

00:29:37.620 --> 00:29:40.060
but now a very changed person.

00:29:40.060 --> 00:29:43.150
Because of the heroic acts,
because of the battles

00:29:43.150 --> 00:29:45.840
that that person had to fight
in the strange world, when they

00:29:45.840 --> 00:29:48.150
come back to the
regular world, they now

00:29:48.150 --> 00:29:50.860
have this extra
amazing knowledge

00:29:50.860 --> 00:29:54.750
that allows that person to
share new insights with people

00:29:54.750 --> 00:29:56.790
in the regular world.

00:29:56.790 --> 00:29:59.420
Now, that was the way
that he described it.

00:29:59.420 --> 00:30:02.290
I think there's a simpler way
that we all know the same idea.

00:30:02.290 --> 00:30:03.600
It says this.

00:30:03.600 --> 00:30:06.910
Whatever doesn't kill
us makes us stronger.

00:30:06.910 --> 00:30:08.394
This is really the
central message

00:30:08.394 --> 00:30:09.560
of the whole hero's journey.

00:30:09.560 --> 00:30:13.370
Now, the hero's journey has
become kind of something that's

00:30:13.370 --> 00:30:14.920
entered into pop
psychology, and it's

00:30:14.920 --> 00:30:16.460
getting kind of beaten
to death and all of that.

00:30:16.460 --> 00:30:17.950
But a lot of people
say, no, no, no, there's

00:30:17.950 --> 00:30:18.940
no such thing as hero's journey.

00:30:18.940 --> 00:30:21.280
Well, let's check and see
if Joseph Campbell might

00:30:21.280 --> 00:30:21.964
have been right.

00:30:21.964 --> 00:30:23.880
And the way I thought
that it would make sense

00:30:23.880 --> 00:30:27.050
to check to see if
this story, this drama,

00:30:27.050 --> 00:30:29.530
actually has power
for us is to look

00:30:29.530 --> 00:30:35.110
at what's popular to look at--
the three most successful movie

00:30:35.110 --> 00:30:38.370
franchises in history
around the world.

00:30:38.370 --> 00:30:40.870
If there's any way
to say, is there

00:30:40.870 --> 00:30:43.270
something that resonates
for people in general

00:30:43.270 --> 00:30:45.170
about this story?

00:30:45.170 --> 00:30:47.910
Well, let's see if this story
carries through the three most

00:30:47.910 --> 00:30:52.214
successful popular stories
pretty much of all time.

00:30:52.214 --> 00:30:53.880
So we're going to
look at three of them.

00:30:53.880 --> 00:30:56.760
One which takes place in the
past, a mythical past, which

00:30:56.760 --> 00:30:58.640
will be of course "The
Lord of the Rings."

00:30:58.640 --> 00:31:01.630
One of these stories takes
place in a mythical present,

00:31:01.630 --> 00:31:03.540
which is "Harry Potter."

00:31:03.540 --> 00:31:05.330
And one of these stories
which takes place

00:31:05.330 --> 00:31:08.570
in a mythical future,
which is "Star Wars."

00:31:08.570 --> 00:31:10.000
And yes, I know.

00:31:10.000 --> 00:31:12.530
I know it begins by
saying, "A long time ago,"

00:31:12.530 --> 00:31:13.280
but let's face it.

00:31:13.280 --> 00:31:15.488
I mean, it's interstellar
travel and it's spaceships.

00:31:15.488 --> 00:31:17.110
It's the future.

00:31:17.110 --> 00:31:19.200
So yes.

00:31:19.200 --> 00:31:22.040
So-- well, you bring
up an excellent point.

00:31:22.040 --> 00:31:24.120
Let's see if this plays out.

00:31:24.120 --> 00:31:25.680
So let's look at
these three stories

00:31:25.680 --> 00:31:27.130
and see if they
all tell something

00:31:27.130 --> 00:31:29.630
that looks like the same story
and some kind of a story that

00:31:29.630 --> 00:31:32.620
might adhere to
this hero's journey.

00:31:32.620 --> 00:31:36.460
So all of these stories
involve the hero

00:31:36.460 --> 00:31:40.180
who is always this
unassuming guy who

00:31:40.180 --> 00:31:44.590
is cast into a new world
against his own desire.

00:31:44.590 --> 00:31:47.070
He just wants to continue
living this happy life,

00:31:47.070 --> 00:31:48.620
but something gets
in front of them

00:31:48.620 --> 00:31:51.180
and forces him to
go into a new world.

00:31:51.180 --> 00:31:54.830
And this story that this
hero is going to experience

00:31:54.830 --> 00:31:56.590
is that he's going
to save the world.

00:31:56.590 --> 00:31:58.526
And in the case of
Frodo, he's going

00:31:58.526 --> 00:31:59.900
to start here in
the happy Shire,

00:31:59.900 --> 00:32:01.120
and then things are
going to get really bad,

00:32:01.120 --> 00:32:02.740
and then he's going to
pop out on the other side.

00:32:02.740 --> 00:32:04.860
In the case of Harry,
he's going to start out

00:32:04.860 --> 00:32:06.500
in the regular world, and things
are going to get really bad.

00:32:06.500 --> 00:32:08.140
Then he's going to pop
out on the other side.

00:32:08.140 --> 00:32:09.350
And in the case of
Luke, he's going

00:32:09.350 --> 00:32:11.530
to start out in this plain
planet that nobody cares,

00:32:11.530 --> 00:32:13.154
and things are going
to get really bad,

00:32:13.154 --> 00:32:15.071
and he's going to pop
out on the other side.

00:32:15.071 --> 00:32:15.570
Interesting.

00:32:15.570 --> 00:32:16.660
They're all telling
the same story,

00:32:16.660 --> 00:32:19.020
and they're all telling it in
almost exactly the same way.

00:32:19.020 --> 00:32:20.330
But one of the
things that's also

00:32:20.330 --> 00:32:21.871
interesting about
this hero's journey

00:32:21.871 --> 00:32:24.460
is that the hero is not alone.

00:32:24.460 --> 00:32:27.720
There are other characters that
are helping on this journey.

00:32:27.720 --> 00:32:30.940
And what's amazing is these
other characters always

00:32:30.940 --> 00:32:33.710
play the same role.

00:32:33.710 --> 00:32:34.860
What do I mean?

00:32:34.860 --> 00:32:38.990
There is always the
sidekick, the goofy character

00:32:38.990 --> 00:32:43.820
who's there to enable the
hero in amazing ways, that's

00:32:43.820 --> 00:32:46.550
a kind soul who stays with the
hero through thick and thin.

00:32:46.550 --> 00:32:49.020
So it's Sam with Frodo,
and it's Ron with Harry,

00:32:49.020 --> 00:32:51.430
and it's Han Solo with Luke.

00:32:51.430 --> 00:32:54.920
And then, as we're getting
near the end, they have a fight

00:32:54.920 --> 00:32:56.790
and the sidekick leaves.

00:32:56.790 --> 00:32:59.970
But the sidekick
always comes back

00:32:59.970 --> 00:33:03.470
at the very last moment,
at the last moment,

00:33:03.470 --> 00:33:05.350
and is the one who
enables the hero

00:33:05.350 --> 00:33:09.060
to finally win, who does the
amazing thing at the end;

00:33:09.060 --> 00:33:13.120
whether it's Sam carrying Frodo
and throwing the ring in there,

00:33:13.120 --> 00:33:16.120
or whether it's Ron saving
Harry in the last battle,

00:33:16.120 --> 00:33:18.680
or whether it's Han Solo flying
in with the Millennium Falcon

00:33:18.680 --> 00:33:21.790
at the last second when when
Luke's flying down the death

00:33:21.790 --> 00:33:25.037
trench and blows up
the Darth Vader ship.

00:33:25.037 --> 00:33:26.120
So there's that character.

00:33:26.120 --> 00:33:27.328
But are there more parallels?

00:33:27.328 --> 00:33:30.290
Yes, because there always has
to be the mentor, who obviously

00:33:30.290 --> 00:33:33.900
it pays to be someone
with a big beard.

00:33:33.900 --> 00:33:36.090
So in the case of "The
Lord of the Rings,"

00:33:36.090 --> 00:33:37.540
we have Gandalf,
who comes along.

00:33:37.540 --> 00:33:39.510
And we've got Dumbledore
in "Harry Potter."

00:33:39.510 --> 00:33:42.710
And we've got Obi
Wan in "Star Wars."

00:33:42.710 --> 00:33:44.340
And it's interesting,
because remember

00:33:44.340 --> 00:33:45.798
what happens in
the hero's journey.

00:33:45.798 --> 00:33:48.190
The hero is in a strange
world, a place where

00:33:48.190 --> 00:33:50.060
they don't know what's going on.

00:33:50.060 --> 00:33:52.720
The job of the mentor is
to guide them and give them

00:33:52.720 --> 00:33:55.960
rules of how the world
works in this strange place.

00:33:55.960 --> 00:34:00.324
So this ancient wizard who knows
the world provides these clues

00:34:00.324 --> 00:34:01.990
and provides information
for how to live

00:34:01.990 --> 00:34:08.770
in this strange world and then
dies, leaving the hero alone;

00:34:08.770 --> 00:34:14.400
but always, again, comes back
to the hero in spiritual form

00:34:14.400 --> 00:34:18.949
at the last possible moment
just before the final climax

00:34:18.949 --> 00:34:20.679
and gives them the
last bit of support

00:34:20.679 --> 00:34:23.146
that they're going
to need to happen.

00:34:23.146 --> 00:34:25.020
And then there is the
princess, because we'll

00:34:25.020 --> 00:34:28.409
notice that so far it's
just been a bunch of dudes.

00:34:28.409 --> 00:34:31.630
So there are the women
in this hero's journey?

00:34:31.630 --> 00:34:33.530
Well, in the classic
hero's journey,

00:34:33.530 --> 00:34:35.620
as it is represented
by Joseph Campbell

00:34:35.620 --> 00:34:37.810
and clearly by these
three most popular movie

00:34:37.810 --> 00:34:40.510
franchises in history,
the woman's role

00:34:40.510 --> 00:34:43.060
is kind of interesting
and kind of weird,

00:34:43.060 --> 00:34:47.070
because there's always this
woman who is a princess.

00:34:47.070 --> 00:34:48.960
And she has some knowledge.

00:34:48.960 --> 00:34:51.020
She kind of has the
keys to what it's really

00:34:51.020 --> 00:34:53.210
going to take to win
this thing, whether it's

00:34:53.210 --> 00:34:55.770
the princess of the elves or
the princess of the muggles

00:34:55.770 --> 00:34:57.700
or the princess of the universe.

00:34:57.700 --> 00:35:00.760
And she's always a
potential love interest

00:35:00.760 --> 00:35:03.600
and always turns out to
be the hero's sister.

00:35:07.310 --> 00:35:09.380
For those of you that are
interested in, is there

00:35:09.380 --> 00:35:10.960
an aspect of the
hero's journey that

00:35:10.960 --> 00:35:13.810
might be more interesting or
appealing from the woman's

00:35:13.810 --> 00:35:16.670
perspective, Joseph Campbell
didn't write anything about it.

00:35:16.670 --> 00:35:17.690
But there are a
lot of people now.

00:35:17.690 --> 00:35:19.250
In fact, there's a woman
whose name is slipping my mind

00:35:19.250 --> 00:35:21.380
right now-- I met her
recently-- at Stanford who's

00:35:21.380 --> 00:35:23.630
looking to see, is there are
a parallel hero's journey

00:35:23.630 --> 00:35:25.820
that might apply from
the woman's perspective?

00:35:25.820 --> 00:35:28.334
The theory being as follows.

00:35:28.334 --> 00:35:30.750
These stories, these great
myths that have stayed with us,

00:35:30.750 --> 00:35:33.166
tended to be the stories that
stayed with us, because they

00:35:33.166 --> 00:35:34.820
were the stories
that got retold.

00:35:34.820 --> 00:35:36.352
So perhaps what
was happening is it

00:35:36.352 --> 00:35:38.060
was the guys who are
retelling the story,

00:35:38.060 --> 00:35:39.890
so their stories
continue to get told.

00:35:39.890 --> 00:35:41.598
The stories that the
women were retelling

00:35:41.598 --> 00:35:43.030
were never getting retold.

00:35:43.030 --> 00:35:44.629
But is there a woman's
hero's journey?

00:35:44.629 --> 00:35:46.170
And there are people
looking into it.

00:35:46.170 --> 00:35:47.710
And it appears
that there may be.

00:35:47.710 --> 00:35:49.760
And it's not exactly
the same as the one

00:35:49.760 --> 00:35:51.195
we're going through now.

00:35:51.195 --> 00:35:52.320
But let's look at this one.

00:35:52.320 --> 00:35:54.970
So are there any other
characters that are the same?

00:35:54.970 --> 00:35:57.980
And as I was doing
this, I was having fun

00:35:57.980 --> 00:36:00.630
taking these stories I know
and getting my little Lego

00:36:00.630 --> 00:36:02.450
characters and lining
them up and saying,

00:36:02.450 --> 00:36:03.640
why are they all the same?

00:36:03.640 --> 00:36:06.265
And it's amazing, because as you
continue through, yes, there's

00:36:06.265 --> 00:36:07.410
always this gentle giant.

00:36:07.410 --> 00:36:10.460
So whether it's Gimli
or Hagrid or Chewbacca,

00:36:10.460 --> 00:36:12.810
again, it pays to have a
really, really big beard

00:36:12.810 --> 00:36:14.090
and to be really hairy.

00:36:14.090 --> 00:36:16.120
And the idea is you're
always a giant, which

00:36:16.120 --> 00:36:19.400
means that initially this
person is very, very scary.

00:36:19.400 --> 00:36:22.030
But then the hero realizes
that really the giant

00:36:22.030 --> 00:36:25.210
just represents someone with
an enormous heart, someone

00:36:25.210 --> 00:36:29.000
with enormous belief who
never wavers in their belief

00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:31.440
and continues to provide the
hero with guidance back to,

00:36:31.440 --> 00:36:34.860
what do you really
believe in your heart?

00:36:34.860 --> 00:36:37.330
And then there's
always the comedy duo.

00:36:37.330 --> 00:36:39.120
There are always
these bumbling twins,

00:36:39.120 --> 00:36:42.580
and they're always twins
who are screwing everything

00:36:42.580 --> 00:36:43.590
up along the way.

00:36:43.590 --> 00:36:44.730
They're comic relief.

00:36:44.730 --> 00:36:47.529
But they're there for a
reason, because whether it's

00:36:47.529 --> 00:36:49.070
merry and pippin,
or Fred and George,

00:36:49.070 --> 00:36:52.100
or R2-D2 and C-3PO stumbling
along, telling these jokes,

00:36:52.100 --> 00:36:56.490
giving us comic
relief, in the end,

00:36:56.490 --> 00:37:00.920
they all we find in
themselves some aspect

00:37:00.920 --> 00:37:03.680
of the heroic journey that
the hero experienced as well.

00:37:03.680 --> 00:37:05.560
And they always,
these bumbling fools,

00:37:05.560 --> 00:37:07.360
surprise themselves
at the end by what

00:37:07.360 --> 00:37:12.730
they are able to accomplish in
spite of their own goofiness.

00:37:12.730 --> 00:37:18.020
Now, there would be no story
if there were no bad guy.

00:37:18.020 --> 00:37:19.900
So there has to be a bad guy.

00:37:19.900 --> 00:37:22.370
And obviously, it pays
if you're a bad guy,

00:37:22.370 --> 00:37:24.412
you wear a black cape.

00:37:24.412 --> 00:37:26.370
That's how people know
that you're the bad guy,

00:37:26.370 --> 00:37:28.430
whether you're Sauron or
whether you're Voldemort

00:37:28.430 --> 00:37:29.810
or whether you're Vader.

00:37:29.810 --> 00:37:31.950
And also, you are not human.

00:37:31.950 --> 00:37:33.650
You do not have a human face.

00:37:33.650 --> 00:37:37.250
You are always masked or
you're so horribly disfigured

00:37:37.250 --> 00:37:39.100
that you don't look
like a human anymore.

00:37:39.100 --> 00:37:41.550
And that's how we know
that you are the villain.

00:37:41.550 --> 00:37:44.690
And you are the person
that the hero must defeat.

00:37:44.690 --> 00:37:47.150
But the bad guy, the villain,
is not there on their own,

00:37:47.150 --> 00:37:50.210
because they always
have an army.

00:37:50.210 --> 00:37:52.290
And this is an army
that is always there

00:37:52.290 --> 00:37:55.530
in countless number,
unbeatable number,

00:37:55.530 --> 00:37:58.672
and, again, is always
masked and always inhuman,

00:37:58.672 --> 00:38:00.630
whether it's the Orcs or
whether it's Dementors

00:38:00.630 --> 00:38:02.500
or whether it's
the stormtroopers.

00:38:02.500 --> 00:38:04.870
And when we first
meet this army,

00:38:04.870 --> 00:38:08.050
we know that they
are unbeatable,

00:38:08.050 --> 00:38:11.570
because there are so many of
them and they are in human.

00:38:11.570 --> 00:38:13.180
But then an amazing
thing happens.

00:38:13.180 --> 00:38:17.000
The moment that you kill the
boss, the entire army-- poof--

00:38:17.000 --> 00:38:18.400
just disappears.

00:38:18.400 --> 00:38:21.620
They all just drop dead right
there, all million of them.

00:38:21.620 --> 00:38:25.070
And it turns out that that army
had no strength other than what

00:38:25.070 --> 00:38:26.589
came to them from their leader.

00:38:26.589 --> 00:38:28.130
The moment you get
rid of the leader,

00:38:28.130 --> 00:38:31.180
the army's completely gone
and the battle is over.

00:38:31.180 --> 00:38:33.740
So why do I take this time
to share this with you?

00:38:33.740 --> 00:38:35.630
Because people pooh-pooh
the hero's journey.

00:38:35.630 --> 00:38:37.960
But, oh no, it is
absolutely right.

00:38:37.960 --> 00:38:40.600
It's almost as if this is
something that is in us.

00:38:40.600 --> 00:38:44.490
This is what a story, this is
what a drama is really about.

00:38:44.490 --> 00:38:46.190
And again, if you
just look at movies,

00:38:46.190 --> 00:38:51.300
you look at pop culture,
almost all of the big movies

00:38:51.300 --> 00:38:55.260
just tell the same story
over and over again.

00:38:55.260 --> 00:38:56.690
We change the characters.

00:38:56.690 --> 00:38:57.890
We change the time.

00:38:57.890 --> 00:38:59.810
Recently, we changed the gender.

00:38:59.810 --> 00:39:02.010
But we're always
telling the same story

00:39:02.010 --> 00:39:03.690
of this person who
doesn't want to be

00:39:03.690 --> 00:39:05.970
in this strange
world, who goes in,

00:39:05.970 --> 00:39:08.670
changes, and comes back out.

00:39:08.670 --> 00:39:09.170
All right.

00:39:09.170 --> 00:39:09.890
So that's kind of cool.

00:39:09.890 --> 00:39:11.056
But what about in real life?

00:39:11.056 --> 00:39:14.110
I mean, does anything about this
ever take place in the world

00:39:14.110 --> 00:39:15.940
that we're in?

00:39:15.940 --> 00:39:17.310
Absolutely.

00:39:17.310 --> 00:39:19.010
Let's think about
this for a moment.

00:39:19.010 --> 00:39:21.440
Do we ever see anything that
happens like this at work?

00:39:21.440 --> 00:39:24.630
So this is, again, our line of
the full hero's journey story.

00:39:24.630 --> 00:39:27.592
This is really our view
of the whole drama.

00:39:27.592 --> 00:39:30.050
And what happens is we start
today where everything's fine.

00:39:30.050 --> 00:39:31.126
Some bad trigger happens.

00:39:31.126 --> 00:39:32.500
We go into this
point of descent.

00:39:32.500 --> 00:39:36.760
We reach this pit of doom
where everything is over.

00:39:36.760 --> 00:39:39.854
And this is, by the
way, is known as death.

00:39:39.854 --> 00:39:41.520
There is nothing
that's worse than this.

00:39:41.520 --> 00:39:42.190
Life is over.

00:39:42.190 --> 00:39:45.410
But then we decide, no,
we're not going to die today.

00:39:45.410 --> 00:39:50.500
We figure out or we remember or
we find something that tells us

00:39:50.500 --> 00:39:52.900
how to begin to get
out of this pit.

00:39:52.900 --> 00:39:54.740
And we began to work
our way back up.

00:39:54.740 --> 00:39:57.660
And as we work our
way out of that pit,

00:39:57.660 --> 00:40:00.680
fighting dragons
along the way, we

00:40:00.680 --> 00:40:03.432
start to get so much energy
that, again, we learn a lesson

00:40:03.432 --> 00:40:04.890
and we come back
on the other side,

00:40:04.890 --> 00:40:08.200
having learned this
entirely new thing.

00:40:08.200 --> 00:40:10.420
But does this ever
really happen?

00:40:10.420 --> 00:40:12.209
Does it ever happen
that there is someone

00:40:12.209 --> 00:40:14.000
who's having a fine
life, and then the life

00:40:14.000 --> 00:40:15.470
takes a turn for the worst.

00:40:15.470 --> 00:40:17.290
And then that someone
becomes very sad,

00:40:17.290 --> 00:40:20.201
because that life is really,
really bad and is just about

00:40:20.201 --> 00:40:21.200
on the verge to give up.

00:40:21.200 --> 00:40:22.210
Has this ever happened?

00:40:22.210 --> 00:40:25.070
And then that person says,
no, I'm not going to give up.

00:40:25.070 --> 00:40:27.080
I'm going to find
something that's

00:40:27.080 --> 00:40:28.660
going to help me
turn this around.

00:40:28.660 --> 00:40:30.930
I'm not going to die today.

00:40:30.930 --> 00:40:32.920
And then that person,
just through the act

00:40:32.920 --> 00:40:36.467
of deciding to try to improve,
finds that things get better,

00:40:36.467 --> 00:40:38.550
and then it comes screaming
out on the other side.

00:40:38.550 --> 00:40:41.030
This happens all the time.

00:40:41.030 --> 00:40:43.060
And this happens in
business all the time.

00:40:43.060 --> 00:40:45.470
This is the way we tell
stories about what we do,

00:40:45.470 --> 00:40:46.430
about business.

00:40:46.430 --> 00:40:50.600
Think about some of our great
business or pop culture heroes.

00:40:50.600 --> 00:40:53.210
One of the reasons that
